Q  The Wampanoag tribe, who helped the Pilgrims adapt to their new home, were not invited to the first Thanksgiving. The Wampanoag had already suffered from the effects of smallpox, which had been brought over by European colonizers. The Wampanoag had also lost a significant number of their people due to the disease. The Wampanoag did not celebrate the first Thanksgiving as a day of joy, but rather as a day of mourning. So the answer is yes. 

